blockAccountVersion(uint256).details: Should any Account implementation version be phased out, this function can be used to block it from being created for new Accounts.Although possible to block an Account version through the versionRoot, that would require verifying the Merkle tree on account creation, which is expensive.

params.version: The Account version to be phased out.

params.guardian_: The address of the new guardian.

createAccount(uint32,uint256,address).details: If accountVersion == 0, the newest version will be used.createAccount() uses the CREATE2 opcode, which can lead to address collision vulnerabilities, as described in: https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-3607. To decrease the probability of finding an address collision, the number of possible account addresses is limited to 2**64. We use a salt with 64 bits, the 32 right most bits of the address of the tx.origin, and 32 bits provided by the user.

params.creditor: The contract address of the creditor.
params.salt: A salt to be used to generate the hash.

returns.account: The contract address of the proxy contract of the newly deployed Account.

returns._0: bool Whether the address is an Account or not.

ownerOfAccount(address).details: Function does not revert when a non-existing Account is passed, but returns zero-address as owner.

pause().details: The pause guardian of the Factory has no cool-down period.

safeTransferAccount(address).details: Adaptation of safeTransferFrom from the ERC-721 standard, where the Account itself triggers the transfer.The Account must do the transferOwnership() before calling this function.The Account itself cannot become its owner.

safeTransferFrom(address,address,address.details: This method transfers an Account on Account address instead of id and also transfers the Account proxy contract to the new owner.The Account itself cannot become its owner.

params.account: The address of the Account that is transferred.

safeTransferFrom(address,address,uint256.details: This method overwrites the safeTransferFrom function in ERC721.sol to also transfer the Account proxy contract to the new owner.The Account itself cannot become its owner.

params.id: The id of the Account that is about to be transferred.

safeTransferFrom(address,address,uint256.details: This method overwrites the safeTransferFrom function in ERC721.sol to also transfer the Account proxy contract to the new owner.The Account itself cannot become its owner.

params.data: additional data, only used for onERC721Received.
params.id: The id of the Account that is about to be transferred.

setBaseURI(string).details: tokenURIs of Arcadia Accounts are not meant to be immutable and might be updated later to allow users to choose/create their own Account art, as such no URI freeze is added.

params.newBaseURI: The new base URI to store.

setNewAccountInfo(address,address,bytes3.details: Changing any of the contracts does NOT change the contracts for existing deployed Accounts, unless the Account owner explicitly chooses to upgrade their Account to a newer version.

params.data: Arbitrary data, can contain instructions to execute when updating Account to new implementation.
params.implementation: The contract address of the Account implementation.
params.registry: The contract address of the Registry.
params.versionRoot_: The Merkle root of the Merkle tree of all the compatible Account versions.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: This method overwrites the transferFrom function in ERC721.sol to also transfer the Account proxy contract to the new owner.The Account itself cannot become its owner.

params.id: The id of the Account that is about to be transferred.

unpause().details: No reason to be able to create an Account if the owner of the Factory did not unpause createAccount().

unpause(bool).details: This function can unpause the creation of new Accounts.Can only update flags from paused (true) to unpaused (false), cannot be used the other way around (to set unpaused flags to paused).

params.createPaused_: "False" when create functionality should be unpaused.

upgradeAccountVersion(address,uint256,by.details: As each Account is a proxy, the implementation of the proxy can be changed by the owner of the Account. Checks are done such that only compatible versions can be upgraded to. Merkle proofs and their leaves can be found on https://www.github.com/arcadia-finance.

params.account: Account that needs to be upgraded.
params.proofs: The Merkle proofs that prove the compatibility of the upgrade from current to new account version.

allAccountsLength().notice: Function returns the total number of Accounts.

blockAccountVersion(uint256).notice: Function to block a certain Account implementation version from being created as a new Account.

changeGuardian(address).notice: This function is used to set the guardian address

createAccount(uint32,uint256,address).notice: Function to create a new Account.

isAccount(address).notice: View function returning if an address is an Account.

ownerOfAccount(address).notice: Returns the owner of an Account.

pause().notice: This function is used to pause the creation of Accounts.

safeTransferAccount(address).notice: Function used to transfer an Account, called by the Account itself.

safeTransferFrom(address,address,address.notice: Function used to transfer an Account between users based on Account address.

safeTransferFrom(address,address,uint256.notice: Function used to transfer an Account between users based on Account id.
Function used to transfer an Account between users based on Account id.

setBaseURI(string).notice: Function that stores a new base URI.

setNewAccountInfo(address,address,bytes3.notice: Function to set a new Account version with the contracts to be used for new deployed Accounts.

tokenURI(uint256).notice: Function that returns the token URI as defined in the ERC721 standard.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).notice: Function used to transfer an Account between users based on Account id.

unpause(bool).notice: This function is used to unpause the creation of Accounts.

upgradeAccountVersion(address,uint256,by.notice: This function allows Account owners to upgrade the implementation of the Account.
